  "title": "M&E Engineer (MRT Construction)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>MRT/LTA Project: Support all M&amp;E site-works involving the preparation and interpretation of specifications, drawings, and regulations for M&amp;E services/ systems/ installations, and the engineering calculations required for the design of projects.</li>\n  <li>Liaises with architects, engineers, landscape architects, environmental scientists, builders, contractors, suppliers, and project owners to ensure design intentions are met.</li>\n  <li>Leads the analysis and interpretation of reports on loading, labour, productivity, quality, materials and performance.</li>\n  <li>Review monthly reports on M&amp;E activities and report to management.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Requirements:</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree/Diploma in Mechanical/Electrical Engineering</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years of M&amp;E working experience with contractors, construction projects and/or building variation works.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of M&amp;E details, working drawings and local construction practices</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If the role resonates with you and your professional experience complements the responsibilities listed, send your resume to <strong>koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com</strong></p>\n<p>Dickson KOH, EA Registration R1103367</p>\n<p>www.bayesrecruitment.com</p>",
